Title: Focus on Aksel Lund Svindal - Dealing with an injury - Behind the Scenes
Description:
Aksel Lund Svindal has been one of the most dominating skiers in recent years and he was planing on continuing his chase for another Overall title in the 2014/15 season. But in October, as he was getting ready for the first race of the season, during an easy game of football with his team his Achilles Tendon snapped. Svindal was taken into surgery hours later and two and a half months later, in January has returned on skis.

Check out this exclusive Behind the Scenes where we chat with him about injuries, skiracing, his team and more!

The FIS Alpine Ski World Cup is the top international circuit of Alpine Skiing competitions staged annually. It is considered the premier competition in alpine ski racing together with the quadrennial Olympic Winter Games and the biennial FIS Alpine World Ski Championships. Some experts event consider winning the World Cup to be athletically a more valuable title than winning gold at the Olympic Winter Games or the World Championships, since it requires a competitor to ski at an extremely high level in several events throughout the season, and not just in one race. Today, the FIS Alpine Ski World Cup races are held primarily at famous ski resorts in the European Alps, along with regular stops in Scandinavia, North America, and Far East Asia. Competitors attempt to score a maximum of points during the season in five events: slalom, giant slalom, super-G, downhill and super combined. The fifth event, super-combined, was introduced in 2005 and generally consists of a shorter downhill race and a one-run slalom. Sometimes the downhill is replaced by a super-G.  Alpine was added to the Olympic winter schedule in 1936.

Title: Damien Walters 2010
Description:
Helping to spread this video, coz he is amazing.
Enjoy

Some info from wiki, who doesn't know anything about him:

Damien Gareth Walters (born April 6, 1982), from Derby, United Kingdom is a professional stuntman, gymnastics  coach and free runner.

He has competed for Great Britain in tumbling, and at his peak, was ranked 4th in the world, winning the European and world championships with the team. He said his first move was a frontflip on his grass when he was 4 or 5, which he subsequently failed, and so his mother took him to train in gymnastics. He has had over 20 years training experience, and currently trains for about 3-4 hours each day.

Damien's tumbling and gymnastics skills mean that many free running moves come naturally to him, and he was first noticed in the community after releasing his 2007 showreel, which featured many free running inspired moves. This video got him scouted by Jackie Chan's stunt agent, and he has now given up on gymnastics to pursue a career being a stuntman, where he is a part of a core group of stuntmen who work for Brad Allan, the first non-asian member of Jackie Chan's stunt team.

Title: Bernhard Braun 12/13 Powder Skiing Austria - Season Edit
Description:
Please subscribe if you like!

Winter 2012 started awesome with heavy snowfalls, cold temperatures and almost no people on the mountain. On my first competition at Axamer Lizum in January I had to change my whole line a few minutes before my run because they closed some parts of the contest face. I went too fast on a cliff and ended up with a shoulder luxation and labrum tear. I stayed at home for a week to baby my arm and the pain was almost blown away, so I decided to wait for the surgery until summer and keep on skiing more passive. It turned out to be a good choice, there where perfect conditions over weeks and we got to ski the deepest powder we have ever seen, right on my birthday in February . Thanks to Toms Boardershop Lindau for the support and everybody else out there, it was a great time!
The surgery went well and I started training for next season, can't wait for it!

Title: Arai RX-7 GP Helmet Specification
Description:
Arai RX-7 GP helmet specification and features

Arai is extremely proud to announce that the new RX-7 GP helmet is one of the very first helmets to meet both ECE Regulation 22-05 and the new SNELL M2010 standard. The RX-7 GP is in all respects the new benchmark in Arai's helmet technology.The RX-7 GP was developed with the SNELL M2010 in sight, one of the most stringent helmet standards for impact-absorption tests, in addition to the mandated ECE Regulation 22-05 standard.

There are, however, considerable differences between the ECE 22-05 and SNELL M2010 requirements. SNELL M2010 requires for instance that any location above the test line is tested by two consecutive impacts, while ECE 22-05 requires a single impact only at specific points on the test head form. This makes the total impact energy absorbed by each test location of the SNELL M2010 standard almost twice as high than the ECE 22-05 tests in some consumer size ranges. In addition, SNELL M2010 impact absorption tests are carried out with hemispherical and bar anvils.

Both anvils are known as harsh to the outer shell performance. Furthermore, to insure the helmet shell is strong enough, shell penetration testing is also required by SNELL M2010, but is missing in the ECE 22-05 standards. The impact-absorption capacity of the Arai RX-7 GP exceeds even that of the famous RX-7 Corsair. Together with its conformity to both the ECE Regulation 22-05 and SNELL M2010 it makes the RX-7 GP a true benchmark in helmet technology. Available sizes: XS-XXL

Title: SRAM Force 22 Review Sale Price & Availability
Description:
Sale Prices and availability of SRAM Force 22 http://glorycycles.com/search.php?search_query=force22&Search=


We go over the changes to the new SRAM Force 22 group and discuss compatibility and performance.

SRAM ironed out the kinks in the original Red group some time back then added a 11th cog and have quickly sent all that technology down to the Force 22 group. But for ceramic bearings and some weight savings it seems that Force 22 is every bit the performer the Red 22 is. We particularly like the feeling of the shifts, the Force 22 levers snap the chain into the desired cog with a very audible and sure feeling.  The longer brake lever and shift paddle are an improvement on earlier force and the hood shape takes it up yet another notch. 

While Campagnolo and Shimano have embraced the new style mid compact 52/36 chainrings SRAM has stuck to it's guns with WiFli mid cage rear derailleur for the Force 22 and some of the most well thought out cassette ratios. SRAM are calling the new 11 speed Red and Force gourps "22" because they claim all 22 gears are usable.  Looking over the available options we really like the way SRAM have done this and with a 16 tooth cog in all the cassettes(but for the 11-32 Wifil) it seems either compact or standard chainrings can be matched to a cassette that perfectly fits any riding style. 

Here for blog review and images http://bit.ly/13OyXGh

Title: SWINGING VOLLEY | How To Hit The Swinging Volley
Description:
Serve myths debunked: Former Top 100 ATP Pro, Jeff Salzenstein, is exposing 3 common myths that could be crippling your serve potential. Most players make at least 1 of these 3 mistakes... Do you?  https://goo.gl/N3FgRZ

The swinging volley is a great tool to add to your tennis training.

It will help you attack the person who moon balls.

The swinging volley is a great weapon to execute once you have your opponent off the court and want to take time away from their defensive shot.

Next time, try having someone toss you high tennis balls to you around the service line so you can work on hitting swinging volleys.

More and more pros are starting to use the swinging volley instead of just letting the ball bounce.

One of the key finishes on the swinging volley is the hand turn.

This is where you will swing across your body and catch the racquet closer to your swing hip of the non dominant side.

Try using the swinging volley next time during your tennis training.

Even try the swinging volley in a match if someone if giving you really high short balls.

Title: Force USA Balance Ball - Core Strength Exercises - Home Balance and Stability Exercises
Description:
Featuring Fitness Model Nicky Jankovic

The Force USA Exercise Balance Ball (similar to a BOSU balance ball) is a balance trainer that is challenging and safe for all levels.

From the elite athlete to weekend warriors trying to stay in shape, the Force USA Exercise Balance Ball helps to strengthen and coordinate your structure including the muscles of your body that you don't see.

The Force USA Exercise Balance Ball targets the core muscles of your body - those muscles around your abdominal and back area - helping you to not only gain strength, trim and tone but to help coordinate your entire body. Virtually any exercise you can perform on the ground can be performed on the Force USA Exercise Balance Ball  - making that exercise More Challenging! More Fun! and More effective!

For all practical purposes, there are no weight restrictions as the Balance Ball is made with a Burst-Resistant material and was designed to be used by professional athletes, some weighing as much as 150kg or more.

You can stand, squat, sit or use it just like you would a step for aerobics.  You can also turn it upside down for an even wider range of functional exercises! The difference is your body has to constantly shift and contract to stay aligned. This not only helps burn more calories, but enhances coordination and balance.
 

    * Durable Anti-Burst exercise ball
    * Helps improve balance, coordination and flexibility
    * Ideal for Core Strength Exercises, Training, Toning, Resistance Exercise and more
    * Safe, durable and easy-to-use


The Force USA Exercise Balance Ball adds FUNctionality to any workout!

Title: America's Serena Williams won Gold Medal with wild dance Moves
Description:
American Serena Williams stormed her way to an Olympic gold medal Saturday, dominating the final against Maria Sharapova of Russia. It is the first individual gold medal for Williams, who has twice won in Olympic doubles.

Williams won the first set, 6-0, in only 30 minutes. She hit only a handful of unforced errors in each set, and feasted on Sharapova's second serve. She won the second set by 6-1, with the entire match taking only a bit more than an hour to complete.

Williams' march to the podium seemed to be at risk of a possible delay when Sharapova manufactured a break point against Williams, thanks in part to a double-fault. But the American found another level of focus, hitting angled shots with such force that Sharapova had no chance to return them.

Video replays gave Sharapova no help either, as a crucial shot by Williams was shown to to have ticked the chalk. Looking up at the replay screen from the grass on Wimbledon's Centre Court, Sharapova's face seemed to be drained of hope as the ball was confirmed to have landed inside the line.

Down 5-1 in the second set, Sharapova showed a further refusal to submit to what by then seemed inevitable, nailing a long baseline down the line for a winner. But even when she engaged Williams in a long, scrambling point, the American found a way to fire the ball well past her reach.

And then, with Williams serving at 5-1 in the second set and up 30-15, she ripped a second serve straight down the center line for an ace, with Sharapova helpless to reach the ball. One point later, it was curtains, and Williams was shrieking in joy, jumping up and down, waving to the crowd, and even dancing a bit.

Sharapova often took time to compose herself between points, seemingly frustrated by her inability to make a dent in Williams' game. By contrast, the American maintained a calm and focused look, only occasionally letting out a yell to hint at how her emotions were building as she neared one of the few remaining landmarks she hadn't yet reached in a storied career.

After the match, Williams seemed at a loss for words to describe her feat, which she accomplished by losing only 17 games throughout the Olympic tournament. She gave Sharapova credit for fighting hard in the match.

"I don't feel invincible," Williams said. "I just feel good about my game. I just practiced so hard, and it was time."

Title: 2011 Governor's Cup - Balboa Yacht Club
Description:
Balboa Yacht Club's 45th annual Governor's Cup International Junior Match Racing Championship will take place July 19 to 24, 2011.

The teams include two from Australia, two from New Zealand, one from
Bermuda, one from the United Kingdom, one from the Virgin Islands and five from California. Two of the members of last year's first place team from San Diego Yacht Club will be competing as well as two from the second place Newport Harbor Yacht Club team. Title: NBA Toronto Raptors vs Indiana Pacers Fri, January 13th, 2012 [L 95-90] Hightlights
Description:
THE CANADIAN PRESS

TORONTO -- A tough week ended for the Toronto Raptors with an air ball, a heart-breaking loss and a head coach taking the blame.

With the Indiana Pacers up 93-90, Toronto backup centre Jamaal Magloire went to the free-throw line with a chance to cut the lead in the final 14 seconds.

Instead, Magloire missed both shots, including one on an ugly air ball that drew boos from the crowd, and had Raptors head coach Dwane Casey putting himself in the firing line after the 95-90 loss Friday.

"It's on me. I take full blame for that," said Casey, who said he should have had Ed Davis on the ball in the situation. "I should have had the flip-flop. I don't think they were intentionally trying to foul. But it happened, I should not have had him handling the ball. ... That's a rookie, not a rookie coach, but that's my mistake."

The foul by Indiana's David West that put Magloire on the free-throw line at a critical moment wasn't intentional, and even West was surprised at who had the ball.

"We said we needed to foul if they got late in the clock, but that was pretty early for him to catch that basketball," said West. "I was just trying to make a play on the ball, be overly aggressive. ... We didn't expect him to have the ball in his hands that moment."

Neither team led by more than two points in the fourth until West's free throw gave Indiana a 91-90 lead. West missed the second shot from the line, but Tyler Hansbrough added two more points after he was fouled grabbing the rebound.

That led to Magloire's free-throw attempts, and after the game the sombre Toronto native wouldn't let Casey take the blame for his missed shots.

"I think that I've been playing this game long enough that I let the team down and I can be accountable as a man and say that I could have did a better job at the free-throw line and as a result we didn't win the game," said Magliore.

The defeat was the Raptors' third in a row during an ugly week that saw them play four games in five nights. But Toronto hardly looked fatigued, and held the lead until the end of the third quarter while also leading the Pacers (8-3) by as many as 16 points in the first half.

Playing without injured star Andrea Bargnani, Toronto's DeMar DeRozan led (4-8) with 23 points, Leandro Barbosa came off the bench to chip in 20 and Jose Calderon added 15 points and nine assists.

Indiana (8-3) meanwhile had to play without star Danny Granger, who was ejected on his second technical foul with 29 seconds left in the second quarter after bumping Davis to the hardwood. Granger stared down Davis and was tossed for it.

Granger left with just four points and one rebound, but the Pacers rallied behind George Hill, who scored 22 points off the bench. Indiana's Roy Hibbert had 15 points and nine rebounds while West and Hansbrough each scored 13.

Granger didn't speak to media after the game, but Pacers head coach Frank Vogel said he was pleased with the way his team responded to the ejection.

"(Toronto is) a tough team to score against," said Vogel. "Hats off to those guys. I'm proud of our guys for grinding out a game that really didn't go our way."

The Raptors looked to DeRozan to fill the scoring void left by Bargnani, who suffered a strained left calf Wednesday against Sacramento. DeRozan answered the call early with 14 points in the first quarter, but cooled off as the game turned in Indiana's favour.

Casey defended DeRozan by pointing to the Pacers' defensive adjustments, while DeRozan added he was trying to play aggressive in Bargnani's absence.

"Things change. You can't stay hot for the whole 48 minutes," said DeRozan. "You got to learn to do other things, rebound, defend, do things like that and try to get your teammates involved. So, it's not really a bad thing. I kind of look at it as a positive."

.James Johnson's alley-oop dunk gave Toronto a 16-point lead in the second, forcing the Pacers to call a timeout to regroup. The breather worked, and Indiana scored eight unanswered points to cut the lead to 40-32, but their momentum was once again hampered by Granger's ejection and trailed Toronto 45-40 at the half.

Calderon's three-pointer with just over five minutes left in the third put the Raptors back up by 10 points, but the Pacers chipped away at the deficit and a driving lay-up by Paul George tied the game at 65 heading into the fourth.

Title: Donald Swanson, Alpha Combat and Boxing's Grassroots Revival
Description:
Boxing may be on the decline in the media marketplace, replaced by Mixed Martial Arts as the combat sport du jour. But for coaches like Donald Swanson, Sam Stern and Joey Regan at Alpha Combat in Mahopac NY,  it's not just about the fight. The physical conditioning and mental stamina needed to excel in all these rough and tumble sports create a  common bond. Another RadXSports video.

Follow and Interact with us on Facebook:
https://www.facebook.com/pages/RadXSports/104138276304120


Narration:
Boxing for three minutes is exhausting. Punching a trash talking trainer who isn't hitting back can wear you down, but a warrior can't give in to fatigue.

There's no conflict between mixed martial arts and boxing in the gym. If there is a conflict between the sports, it's in the marketing. Athletes in all the combat sports practice and respect all the disciplines.

People from all over come to work out for a wide range of reasons.

We asked what it would take to bring boxing from the grass roots back to the big time. Interact with us on Twitter @RadXSports

Lyon, France hosted the 2013 IPC Athletics World Championships between
19-28 July. More than 1,100 athletes from 98 countries attended the
event which was the first major gathering of international track and
field stars following the hugely successful London 2012 Paralympic
Games. The majority of medal winners from London competed in Lyon as
they started their preparations for the next Paralympic Games in Rio in
2016.



The International Paralympic Committee (IPC) is the global governing
body of the Paralympic Movement, and also acts as the International
Federation for nine sports, including athletics. The sport is governed
by the IPC and co-ordinated by the IPC Athletics Sports Technical
Committee, offering a wide range of competitions and events for male
and female athletes in all impairment groups.



For further information, please visit
http://www.paralympic.org/athletics,

The International Paralympic Committee (IPC) is committed to enabling
Paralympic athletes to achieve sporting excellence and to develop sport
opportunities for all persons with a disability from the beginner to
elite level. In addition, the IPC aims to promote the Paralympic
values, which include courage, determination, inspiration and equality.

This is my artistic inline routine 2009. The first time I tried the Open Inline class to get the benefit of choosing any VOCAL music. Technically my routine isn't glamorous, but it is innovative and unique and matches what the song is about.
 
I loved skating it, but Im still working on it to make it better and skate it in a different class in the state competition.

Here is a word of warning. If you should try anything like it, be prepared to pay for it in terms of deduction to the B-marks (artistic impression). Every time I went on the floor I received a deduction of 0.3 points, resulting in a total of -0.9, which does not consider the beginning floor routine as its allowed to be on the ground once. 
 
The music is by Mira, titled 'The Garden'. It is a gloomy song which only carries voice and a strong beat. Its one of the songs, which are very unique.

Title: Juliane Schenk (GERMANY) VS Saina Nehwal (INDIA) Djarum Indonesia Open 2013
Description:
Juliane Schenk (GERMANY) VS Saina Nehwal (INDIA) Djarum Indonesia Open Super Series 2013

About the Djarum Indonesia Open :

Turnamen dunia terbesar dan paling ditunggu para pecinta bulutangkis tanah air, Djarum Indonesia Open Super Series Premier (DIOSSP) 2013 siap digelar. Tak tanggung-tanggung, kejuaraan bulutangkis level teratas ini akan dihelat selama tujuh hari berturut-turut di Istora Senayan, Jakarta, 10-16 Juni mendatang.
 
Mengusung tema "Pride Of The Nation", kejuaraan ini akan diikuti para pebulutangkis top dunia. Sebut saja Lee Chong Wei, Li Xuerui, Mathias Boe/Carsten Mogensen, Wang Xiaoli/Yu Yang, dan Xu Chen/Ma Jin.
 
Sementara, sejumlah nama besar pebulutangkis Indonesia seperti Sony Dwi Kuncoro, Rian Agung Saputro/Angga Pratama, Pia Zebadiah Bernadeth/Rizki Amelia Pradipta, Tontowi Ahmad/Liliyana Natsir, dan Muhammad Rijal/Debby Susanto yang masuk ranking 10 dunia juga dipastikan ikut berpartisipasi dalam ajang kejuaraan bergengsi ini.
 
Tahun lalu, Indonesia berhasil menyabet satu gelar juara dari nomor tunggal putra yang diraih Simon Santoso. Saat itu, Simon berhasil mengakhiri paceklik gelar di sektor tunggal di Indonesia Open selama empat tahun. Ia sukses menumbangkan pemain Cina, Du Pengyu pada partai final lewat skor 21-18, 13-21, 21-11.
 
Tentunya, dalam gelaran Djarum Indonesia Open Super Series Premier 2013 kali ini Indonesia berharap dapat memetik lebih banyak gelar. Diunggulkan di tempat kedua, pasangan ganda campuran, Tontowi/Liliyana yang menjadi runner up tahun lalu berpeluang mencetak gelar juara.
 
Selain itu, di nomor ganda putra, Indonesia memiliki pasangan Rian Agung Saputro/Angga Pratama yang sedang dalam performa prima. Tahun ini, Rian/Angga sukses mengumpulkan dua gelar juara sekaligus dalam dua pekan berturut-turut, yaitu juara Yonex Australia Open GPG dan New Zealand Open Grand Prix. Mereka pun menyajikan aksi memukau di turnamen Piala Sudirman yang digelar baru-baru ini. Rian/Angga berhasil meruntuhkan ganda senior China, Cai Yun/Fu Haifeng dengan skor 19-21, 21-18, dan 21-15, dalam pertandingan dramatis di stadion Putra Bukit Jalil, Kamis, (23/5).
 
Jalannya pertandingan Djarum Indonesia Open Super Series Premier 2013 akan disiarkan langsung oleh Trans 7 dari mulai putaran perdelapan final hingga final, 13-16 Juni. Tak hanya itu, pecinta bulutangkis pun dapat menyaksikan pertandingan via live streaming setiap harinya di www.djarumbadminton.com. Bagi yang ingin menonton langsung di Istora Senayan, tiket dapat dibeli online di www.blibli.com dan on the spot.: 


Untuk informasi lebih lengkap dari Djarum Indonesia Open Super Series Premier, bisa akses di website www.djarumbadminton.com

Title: Hobie Tandem Island Kayak - Storage and Car Topping Part 1
Description:
This video shows the way our Kayak is stored and the loaded onto the top of our 4WD with the help of hoists.

The storage platform enables gear etc to also be raised to the ceiling with the Kayak.
The eye hooks etc are bolted into the roof trusses and I have added cross beams in the roof to distribute the weight.Here's a link to a video of just the platform itself: http://youtu.be/95TIpZALtEo


The loading onto the 4wd is a 4 step process.
1. Raise the island to above the roof bar height.
2. Pull out the sliding bars and insert the extendable poles for added strength. 
3. Fold down the "A" frame hoist. (A key benefit of this design is that the hoist does not raise the height of the vehicle. The A frame folds down between the standard Thule cross bars.
4. Slide the kayak across onto the roof bars, tie down and slide the support bars back into their tubes.

Description:
Highlights from the inaugural Paddy Rally on 28th May 2010. Petrolheads and Celebrities including Stavros Flatley, Footballer Gerry Armstrong and Mr Paparazzi, Darryn Lyons started the day in Belfast with a Police escort from Stormont Parliament Buildings to the border (the Police led the convoy with a tuned Evo), followed by a clear run down to Mondello Park Racing Track in Dublin.

The track day saw us giving the cars full throttle and improving our lap times, as well as demonstrations from the 2009 European drift car champion Mark 'Sidewaysbuff' Luney.

Title: How To: Tie a Figure 8 Knot
Description:
The Figure 8 is one of the most versatile knots for kayakers, rafters, canoeists, swiftwater rescue professionals, climbers and other outdoor folks to learn and use. It works for making a tiedown point along a length of rope and as a stopper knot at the end of one. It's frequently tied at the end of a rescue line to secure it to an anchor point or a rescue belt, often with a carabiner. Climbers use it to securely tie into a climbing harness. You can also tie two different lengths of rope together with it. And a great thing about this knot is that it's easy to untie, even after it's been under load.

Spend some time practicing your knot tying; you can't be on the water all the time! Ropes are an essential part of a boater's gear inventory. They're used for lashing gear into or onto the boat. They tie you up to shore. They're essential for setting up a z-drag and other rescue and safety systems. To do just about anything with a rope requires putting knots in it.   

In this video, NRS Repairs Guru Josh Gile demonstrates different ways of tying the great Figure 8 Knot.

Title: Video 3 of Wushu Masters from China on the Peace Friendship and Health tour.
Description:
Martial Arts (Wushu or Kongfu) is a traditional sport in China which becomes increasingly popular. It is highly valued, especially for the spirit of harmony and self-improvement which results among the practitioners, in addition to the health benefits.

Per invitation of the Ambassador of China to the United Nations, the General Administration of Sport of China and the Chinese Wushu Association is planning to send a martial arts group composed of 20 top athletes for a tour in the United States to promote world peace and to encourage cultural and sport exchange between China and the U.S.A.

Schedule and Highlights of the Tour are as follows:
1. Duration: August 11 to 20, 2011
2. The event title: Chinese Martial Arts Delegation Tour in the United States
3. The organizers:
International Wushu Federation, the General Administration of Sport of China, the Chinese Olympic Committee, the Chinese Wushu Association, the United States Martial Arts Federation, the United Nations (U.N.) Department of Public Information, the Permanent Mission of China to the U.N., the Ministry of Culture of China and so on.
The supporters:
the Embassy of China in the U.S.A., Consulate-General of China in Washington, D.C., the Consulate-General of China in New York, Consulate-General of China in Houston.
The co-organizers:
The Association of Chinese Professionals in Atlanta, Emei Martial Arts Kung Fu School in the US, Sino-US experimental school.

4. Performances:
* The first stop: Washington, D.C. (August 11-15, 2011)
2011 Martial Arts Night in Washington, D.C. (August 14)
* The second stop: New York (August 16-18, 2011)
2011 U.N. Martial Arts Night (August 18 evening, at the General
Assembly Hall)
* The third stop: Atlanta (August 19-20)
2011 Martial Arts Night in Atlanta (August 19 evening)

5. The martial arts show:
The show will be performed by the best Wushu athletes and hundreds of wushu amateurs from China and the U.S. The content is captivating, including the chic and beautiful Chang Quan (Quan: fist-boxing), the vigorous Nan Quan, the smooth Taichi, the exciting sparring and Sanda (free sparring), and other magnificent collective performances. The event will showcase traditional and modern martial arts which will reflect the spirit of harmony and health, and enable attendees to feel the charm of Wushu and to appreciate Chinese culture

Title: HOW TO WRAP YOUR HANDS FOR BOXING - BASICS WITH COACH NELSON
Description: HI IM COACH NELSON WITH SUPREME TEAM BOXING. HERE I AM GOING TO SHOW YOU A GREAT WAY TO WRAP YOUR HANDS. IT IS VERY IMPORTANT TO WRAP YOUR HANDS BEFORE PUTTING ON BOXING GLOVES. IT WILL HELP PREVENT INJURIES. YOU WANT TO START OFF HIGH AT THE WRIST, 2-3 TIMES AROUND. THEN GO AROUND YOUR KNUCKLES 2-3 TIMES. THEN GO BACK UP TOWARDS THE WRIST AND AROUND YOUR THUMB. THEN AROUND THE KNUCKLES AGAIN. NEXT BACK UP TOWARDS THE WRIST AND THEN TAKE IT THROUGH YOUR FINGERS ONE AT A TIME. NEXT AROUND THE KNUCKLES, THEN YOU WANT TO FORM AN "X" ACROSS YOUR HAND. THEN AGAIN AROUND THE KNUCKLES, THEN TOWARDS THE WRIST. NEXT CLOSE YOUR HAND TIGHT AND FINISH OFF AROUND THE WRIST.

Title: Demarini LC Legend vs. Miken MV1
Description: Believe it or not once I adjusted to the flexiness of the demarini it was hitting balls almost as far as the mv1.  As I went back and looked at the video, the 3 that went out weren't even my hardest swings, adding to the theory that the flexy helps on a more deliberate swing as opposed to sheer bat speed.  It is interesting to note that the LC legend broke 10 cuts after this bp session so all in all it lasted maybe 200 swings with about 30 being hot.  And by hot I mean almost as hot as the mv1.  So IMO these bats should cost as much as combats since combats are hot affordable yet not very durable.

Title: Swans TV - Swans IN FOCUS Episode 35
Description:
. . . Swans In Focus is packed with features from in and around the Liberty as we bring you the latest episode. 
Ecuadorian winger Jefferson Montero is the centre of attention in this week's Swans Catch Up interview as he brings us up to speed on his time at the Liberty so far. 
There are goals galore in our highlights package of Swans' Under-21s clash with Brentford earlier this week in Griffin Park. 
And we head to Baglan as club ambassador Lee Trundle and Swans midfielder Jack Cork get involved in one of the club's hugely successful half-term soccer camps.





Swansea City Association Football Club is a Welsh professional football club based in the city of Swansea, South Wales that plays in the Premier League. Swansea City represent England when playing in European competitions, although they have represented Wales in the past. They play their home matches at the Liberty Stadium.
The club was founded in 1912 as Swansea Town and joined the Football League in 1921. The club changed their name in 1969, when it adopted the name Swansea City to reflect Swansea's new status as a city.
In 1981, the club were promoted to the original Football League First Division. It was during the following season they came close to winning the league title, but a decline then set near the season's end before finishing sixth, although a club record. It was from here the club suffered a relegation the season after, returning to the Football League Fourth Division a few seasons later, then narrowly avoided relegation to the Football Conference in 2003. Prior to playing home matches at the Liberty Stadium, the team had previously hosted at the Vetch Field. The Swansea City Supporters Society Ltd owns 20% of the club, with their involvement hailed by Supporters Direct as "the most high profile example of the involvement of a supporters' trust in the direct running of a club".
In 2011, Swansea were promoted to the English Premier League, becoming the first Welsh team to play in the top division since its formation in 1992. On 24 February 2013, Swansea beat Bradford City 5-0 to win the 2012-13 Football League Cup (the competition's highest ever winning margin for the final), winning the first major English trophy in the club's history and qualifying for the 2013-14 UEFA Europa League.

Title: Fernando Torres of Anfield - The world's best striker
Description:
A compilation of Fernando Torres, striker of Liverpool Football Club and the Spanish national team. 

Liverpool bought Torres for around 20 million euros, a club record, in the summer before the 2007-08 season. That season, Torres scored his 24th premier league goal in the last game of the season. He set a new record for the most prolific foreign goal scorer ever in a debut season in England, beating Ruud van Nistelrooy's 23. He ended the season in joint second place with Emmanuel Adebayor of Arsenal in the race for the Premier League Golden Boot. Ever since, Torres has become an irreplacable part of the Liverpool squad. On December 29, 2009, he became the fastest player to score 50 goals for Liverpool after his stoppage- time winner against Aston Villa. He made his 100th appearance for the Reds against Wigan on December 16, 2009, scoring his 61st goal for Liverpool.

Torres also is key to the Spanish national team. He forms a deadly partnership with Valencia striker David Villa. The high point of his international career came in the Euro 2008 tournament. He scored the winning goal in the final against Germany, Spain winning 1-0. He has also helped Spain in qualifying for this years FIFA World Cup Finals in South Africa.

Title: Nakamura wins a Queen  and the 2009 Chess Championship of the USA!
Description:
More info about this tournament go to: http://www.thechessdrum.net/blog/2009/05/07/2009-us-championship-st-louis/

Right after this final game of the 2009 US Chess Championship, I was able to speak with Nakamura outside the chess club on a beautiful blue clear sky afternoon in St Louis, Mo.  If you are in st louis, you must visit the club! On the website you will find video of GM lectures! Nakamura has just moved to St Louis!

The 2009 Champion was in a good mood! I took the moment and asked him a few personal questions and I think I took him by surprised, but he answered me anyway.  You have to respect this guy, he is not the type to duck a question.

I discovered Nakamura is American, however his father was born in Japan.  I have the feeling his father might think chess is a child's game because I have heard him talk about other professions where a lot of money can be earned.  

What other country can claim such fame!?  He told me that chess was not that popular in Japan and another game is, a name I can not remember now.  I got the feeling from talking with the new American Champ he has eyes on a bigger prize! So, America is proud of our 2 time Champion!!!! No American has won the World Title since Bobby Fisher in 1972. 

For the press:
Nakamura states,"This is a title that means so much to me and the U.S. chess community - and I have to thank the Chess Club and Scholastic Center of Saint Louis for putting on such a memorable championship. Winning the second title feels better to me than the first."

Nakamura employed an opening that was frequent in the repertoire of the great champion Bobby Fischer. Friedel was not cautious enough and allowed his Queen to finish trapped on move 21, after which he immediately resigned. (from chessdom.com)

Nakamura states, "I dont completely understand my style, nowadays in certain dynamic positions my attitude is generally: Ill play anything, and to keep it complicated. Outside of my opponent's theory, Im a jack of all trades. 

I could never live in Europe, Ill definitely be staying in the US."
Unquote. and the USA is proud of its new chess champion!!!

Title: 320 x 2 x 8 - Ed Coan Bench Press Program - Week 4 (at 229.8 lbs)
Description:
Hit my bench workout a day early since I need to deadlift tomorrow before I go on vacation on Thursday.  Therefore, I didn't do any upper body this past weekend and I felt quite fresh and strong going into this workout.  

I was going to hit 315 lbs for 2 sets of 8, but I decided to challenge myself with 320 lbs instead.  

Also, I had upped the close-grips to 280 lbs (5 lbs more than the first time through), but I decided that would be too easy....so I went with 285 lbs instead.  It was still too easy....I made the second set of 285 lbs harder by not resting much in between....you see a big difference between the two sets.  

As for inclines, I planned to up the weight by 5 lbs over the first cycle, but decided to increase it another 5 lbs today...so 265 lbs was the working weight.  This was a great challenge....especially on the second set.  

Here's how it went:

Bench Press

320 lbs x 2 x 8 Reps (@9 maybe 8 on the first set)

Close-Grips

285 lbs x 8 Reps (@7)
285 lbs x 8 Reps (@9 didn't take much rest to make this set harder)

Incline Bench Press

265 lbs x 8 Reps (@8)
265 lbs x 8 Reps (@9)

It was a solid workout.  I am looking forward to hitting lower reps now....

Title: The Air Force Football Experience (vs Navy 2010)
Description:
When you visit Colorado Springs on a Saturday in the fall and head to the Air Force Academy for a football game, don't expect to experience the same wild and rowdy crowds you'd find in The South. You aren't going to run into a bunch of drunk fans. Meanwhile, Air Force does have value, namely in tradition. 

Particularly when they face Army or Navy at home, the experience can be even better. These scenes were in October of 2010 when Air Force hosted Navy. Pay attention to many traditions illustrated here; the falcon flying from atop the stadium to midfield, the "Air-Force" chant, cadets doing push ups after touchdowns and other things that make Air Force special. 

I'm not a cadet, nor a member of the military, but I'm more than thankful for what these cadets have done for America and their courage. Go Air Force - Sink Navy!

Today we're going to go over a dumbbell kick, otherwise known as a dumbbell kickback. It's for your triceps. It's a very basic exercise for your triceps, a well-known exercise that you can do completely right or completely wrong. There are many different things that go into such a simple exercise. First, you can do these standing, or you can do these kneeling. The most popular way to do them is on a bench. I still prefer that way, too. 

You want your knee well-supported, and you want your body well-supported. This arm is for your upper-body support. The back leg is firmly on the ground. You want good balance. You're going to choose a weight that you can control through the motion without cheating. I like to stay light with these. You're not really going to go heavy; it's a concentrated exercise. With this starting position, you never want to lock out. You're going to keep a slight bend in your elbow. Now, your elbow is going to start here. You want to keep your upper arm at 90 degrees to the floor, parallel to the floor, the whole time. 

As you do this exercise, you simply extend the elbow out and bring it back. It's a very controlled exercise. To get the most out of it, you're going to come up and pause. That really works the muscle, right there. That pause is what you're going to feel the most. Now release back down. It's not a swing thing. That's totally wrong; it's cheating, and you're not doing a thing for your muscle. It's all controlled. Squeeze that muscle and return. Squeeze that muscle, and return. Really pump a lot of blood into that. This isn't a heavy exercise. It's something you want to keep light. You can really fill that muscle up with blood and get the nutrients that you need. 

Again, you see a lot of guys have bad form with this, where they torque their bodies to cheat the exercise and basically make it an ego exercise. This is not an ego exercise at all. The better control you have doing it, the better results you're going to get. You're square with the ground, you're firm with your feet, your hands, and support. Elbows are parallel to the floor. Come up, squeeze that muscle. Make it burn, and return. Come up, squeeze that muscle. Make it burn, and return. And that's your tricep kickback.

Title: ULTRAS KELANTAN experiment frame by frame
Description:
SONG BY KHOTTAL.
(RANDOM EDITING, JUST FOR EXPERIMENT)

selepas kami menyiapkan video ini, kami dapati ia bukanlah sekadar satu video atau yeknik editing yang boleh kita ceritakan atau rungkaikan, samaada seronok atau tidak. ia juga boleh digunakan sebagai penceritaan kepada manusia bagaimana konsep brotherhood itu berlaku. ini dapat dikesan melalui teknik editing yang berkaitan bingkai gambar dan masa (frame/second). bingkai gambar dan masa haruslah selari atau temponya juga perlulah dijaga supaya tidak mengganggu konsentrasi penonton. jika salah satu bingkai gambar kurang, ia akan menyebabkan visual kelihatan seakan lompat dari satu bingkai ke satu bingkai. disini, ia menerangkan bahawa bagaimana sikap brotherhood itu berkaitan dengan sikap saling melengkapi dan setiap manusia itu punyai kelebihan masing-masing. selain itu, pelbagai sudut dari video ini boleh dilihat dan di kaitkan dengan kehidupan semasa jika anda melihat video ini secara pelbagai, ia berkaitan dengan latihan minda anda yang cepat menangkap sesuatu keadaan lalu di terjemahkan kepada kehidupan seharian. video ini melibatkan tiga medium iaitu gambar,video dan audio. ia boleh dikelsifikasikan sebagai kehidupan biasa manusia yang melihat alam sekeliling(video) dan cuba memperingati sesuatu peristiwa di alam minda(gambar) sambil di dendangkan segala macam bunyi disekeliling(audio)

salam hormat kepada semua pengkarya yang terlibat didalam video ini, secara langsung mahupun tidak, anda sungguh bertuah kerana mempunyai karya yang secara tak langsung mencipta sejarah tersendiri. dan video pada kali ini menyentuh karya anda dan membawa bersama mengalir ke kaca mata yang lebih ramai melalui sesawang. TERUSKAN PERJUANGAN.

Title: Woodward West Visits Los Angeles Maria Cardenas Skatepark
Description:
Jake Kinney, Beaver Fleming, and Richie Velasquez decided to trek down to Los Angeles, Maria Cardenas Skatepark, in Panorama City, California. 

The Woodward West Staff hosted several Woodward Styled contests which included longest ollie, kickflip challenge, bank jam, ledge jam, and a rail Jam. The locals were stoked and the vibe was like no other. 

Woodward came through with tons of prizes and everyone went away with a little something. This contest was opened to anyone that wanted to compete no matter what your discipline was. Here we were able to capture the local skateboard scene in North Los Angeles and give back to a group locals. 

Special thanks to the staff at the skatepark that helped us organize this. We hope to provide this several times again to other Los Angeles Skateparks. See you soon at a Skatepark near you!

Title: Broomball
Description:
This video was taken on December 7th, 2009, at a match between the "Flippers" and "Sam-n-Andy's" in Whitehorse, Yukon, Canada. I wanted to put this up because as a kid growing up in Whitehorse, I watched this game played alot, but in Washington State, where I now live, it's always shocked me to see how unknown this sport is. I generally explain it as a cross between lacrosse and ice hockey, but even that is confusing to understand. So, I thought maybe this video would help, at least a little. Enjoy!

[From Wikipedia Article] 
Broomball is a popular recreational ice game originating in Canada and played around the world. It is played in a hockey rink, either indoors or outdoors, depending on climate and location. Broomball is very popular in the Canadian province of Manitoba, where Saint-Claude is the Broomball Capital of the World. Broomball is also gaining popularity around the world, particularly in the United States, Australia, and Japan.

In a game of broomball there are two teams, each consisting of six players: a goaltender and five others. The object of the game is to score more goals than your opponent. Goals are scored by hitting the ball into your opponent's net using your broom. Tactics and plays are similar to those used in sports such as ice hockey, roller hockey and floorball.

Players hit a small ball around the ice with a stick called a "broom." The broom may have a wooden or aluminum shaft and has a rubber-molded triangular head similar in shape to that of a regular broom. Players wear special rubber-soled shoes instead of skates, and the ice is prepared in such a way that it is smooth and dry to improve traction.

Outside North America, broomball is often mistaken for the sport of curling, possibly due to the "broom" reference in the name, although the only similarities between the two is that they are both played on ice, and that players do not wear ice skates.

B-1 TAYLOR

DE LA SALLE QB ANTHONY SWEENEY OUT THIS GAME AND IN COMES CHRIS VANDERKLUGT... AND RIGHT OFF THE BAT HE'LL DIVE INTO THE ENDZONE FOR A 14-NOTHING LEAD EARLY IN THE FIRST....

NOW CHECK THIS OUT... SPARTAN DEFENSE PLAYING WELL BUT JESUIT MAKES IT HAPPEN HERE... COLE BROWNHOLTZ PASSING... DEFLECTED INTO THE ARMS OF CHRISTIAN DYER... THAT DRIVE WAS STALLED..

THEN ON THE NEXT MARAUDERS POSSESSION IT'S DLS DOING THEIR THING... AND THEIR THING IS SCORING... A LOT.... CAMERON LIS-AH-RUE STEPS IN FRONT OF THE PASS AND A DUDE WITH THE NUMBER 65 IS GONNA SCORE!...  THAT MAKES IT 28-NOTHING...

DLS SO GOOD THEY SHOULD MAKE A MOVIE ABOUT THEM... OH YA... THEY DID... IT'S OUT... 

2ND HALF WENT A WHOLE LOT LIKE THE FIRST... NOT TO GIVE YOU THE SPOILER OR ANYTHING... BUT... YA... ANTOINE CUSTER SCOOTS ACROSS THE GOALINE...

BACKUPS ARE IN NOW BUT IT MAKES NO DIFFERENCE TO THE MACHINE THAT IS THE DE LA SALLE SPARTANS... NICK LOPEZ WITH THE LONG RUN HERE AND IT'S 49 TO NOTHING...

BUT JESUIT BEGINS THEIR COMEBACK LATE!!!!!  THAT'S ACTUALLY NOT TRUE... I MADE THAT UP... INSTEAD, RIGHT HERE IT SAYS, LOPEZ WITH ANOTHER LONG TOUCHDOWN... WE'LL JUST STICK TO THE SCRIPT...  AS DOES DE LA SALLE... 63-NOTHING FINAL SCORE AS THE SPARTANS START THEIR BACKUP QB BUT CHRIS VANDERKLUGT MAKES A DAY OF IT...

Title: Captain Bullet
Description: This climb has been on my tick list for 8 years.  it is a sweet little 13b at Maple Canyon that I tried only once 8 years ago.  The climbing was super fun, and I had my moves sussed back then.  I left the draws on the thing overnight, and decided to try the next morning.  When I got to the climb, the draws had been STOLEN!  I was disgusted and didn't go back to Maple for many years.  This year we finally made it back, and it is soooo good.  So much more developed and even better than I remember.  I've heard many snobbish climbers say they don't enjoy the climbing there since cobble pulling is uninteresting and tedious.  Go try Captain Bullet.  If I had had crash pads, I would have bouldered it, and I am sure that this has been done since it is only V8ish.  What a great climb!  I thought it would be easy since my power is pretty decent nowadays, but it still took more than a couple tries over a couple days.  I even had 2 ground falls on the thing! (Barely touched, excellent belay by my French slave, David Labrosse.  This climb is right off the road as you drive up the canyon past the Box on the right.  it is shaded by aspens, but is best climbed in the early morning or late evening in summer.  There is a vicious techy kneebar, so bring a good kneepad.  Thanks to my sponsors for many years of support of the climbing community, please buy their products, I do.

Title: Thermal City Highbanking June 1
Description: Me testing out an earlier version of a wood drop riffle high banker I had built. Took it to thermal city to test with. The grizzly 4 mesh screen was good for washing and inspecting the rocks but it caused the rocks to hang up. Newer version has a bar grizzly instead of the mesh and plastic water deflectors channeling all the material and water from the top grizzly into the bottom sluice. Also I changed the top grizzly so the angle of both sections is now the same. The first section of the high banker has 12 inches of miners moss and raised expanded metal with grooved carpeting underneath the grizzly. Second section of the sluice is just 1/2 inch drop riffles with 1/8 inch smaller drops inside them, by 3 feet long.

Title: Miami Heat 103 vs 73 Brooklyn Nets_Full highlights//11-07-2012
Description:
MIAMI -- In 25 seasons of Miami Heat basketball, the club had never won its first four home games of any season.
And the Heat are making it look easy.
Dwyane Wade scored 22 points on 10-for-14 shooting, LeBron James finished two assists shy of a triple-double, and the Heat clamped down defensively again to beat the Brooklyn Nets 103-73 on Wednesday night.

Miami scored 31 points off Brooklyn turnovers, and starting with the final minute of the first half, the Heat outscored the Nets 57-32.

"When we get stops, we're going to break open a lot of games because we can score," James said. "So that's the No. 1 key."

James had 20 points and 12 rebounds in only 30 minutes, and Rashard Lewis came off the bench to score 13 points on 6-for-9 shooting for the Heat (4-1). Miami -- which plays its next six games on the road -- has won its four home games by an average of 17.8 points.

Kris Humphries had a double-double by halftime, then was silent in the second half and finished with 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Nets (1-2). Deron Williams scored 14 for Brooklyn, which got 12 off the bench from MarShon Brooks.

"It was just an off night because we had a lot of open looks," said Nets guard Joe Johnson, who finished 4 for 14 with nine points. "I know I did and I missed a few myself. Other than that it was just shots that we normally make that we didn't make tonight. Against a good team like Miami, you have to make them pay."

Miami started 3-0 at home in four other seasons, always falling in the fourth game. Not this time. The Nets held the lead four times in the opening quarter, but all by one point and lasting a total of 2:33.

Other than that, all Miami. The Heat started 3 for 12 from 3-point range, then made seven of their last 12, giving them 40 makes from beyond the arc in their last three games.

"They're tough when you're turning the ball over," Nets coach Avery Johnson said. "I thought there were times when we got our half-court defense set that we were decent. We got the ball out of LeBron's hands some, out of Wade's hands some, but then we didn't recognize their shooters and their shooters made shots tonight."

The Heat shot 52 percent, holding New Jersey to 38 percent. Miami finished with 25 assists and 12 turnovers; New Jersey finished with 12 assists and 19 turnovers.

"It was good to see another game, sub-40 percent," Heat coach Erik Spoelstra said. "Our guys were, for the most part, committed to try to make an impact on that side of the floor."

Brooklyn didn't lose sight of Miami in the first half, still being within five with less than a minute remaining until the break, before the Heat got late scores from Wade and James to take a 50-41 edge into the locker room.

And as was the case against Phoenix (with a 23-6 run) on Monday, the Heat used the third quarter as the springboard.

It was a 54-46 game after Keith Bogans made a 3-pointer for Brooklyn early in the third, but after that, it was all Heat. Miami needed just 91 seconds to put together a 10-0 run -- two baskets by Wade started it, and 3-pointers from Shane Battier and Mario Chalmers finished it, putting the Heat up 64-46.

"We know there's going to be moments when you're not going to be able to shoot the ball as well as you want to," Wade said. "It averages out for this team. ... That's why you have to be a good defensive team to be successful in this league."

The outcome was never again in doubt. Chalmers extended the lead to 20 when he sliced down the lane for a nifty layup with 3:45 left in the third, and James made a stepback 3-pointer as time was running out in the period for what was then Miami's largest lead, 79-56.

By then, the only drama was whether James would get his 33rd regular-season triple-double, which would have been his first since March 29, 2011.

Instead, he remained on the bench in the fourth, the Heat comfortably ahead the whole way.

"One, I didn't know," Spoelstra said. "Two, that's not the time to put him back in. We're thinking big picture."

Title: 180 Stand up slide tutorial
Description: This is a slide tutorial on how to do a 180 stand up slide heelside. Board set up. Bustin Ibach 9ply, 50cal 50degree caliber trucks (precision type/ downhill setup with hard barrel bushings used in precision trucks), 10 degree reduction khiro wedge, 86a Orangatang morongas. Wear a helmet. As you can tell this was all shot in one take, using slide gloves as a stand for the camera. clarification this is a video on how to slow stand up slide. stand up slides at comfortable cruising speeds i.e. 20 mph can be done easily by simply pushing with back foot and rotating shoulders. both frontside and backside. this is for when you are going slowly at five miles and hour or so and you wanna switch board around or if you wanna show off to your friends that you can slide goin super slow.

Title: Greba i Enes prica o VULTURESIMA.wmv
Description:
U samom pocetku sve je to bilo neorganizovano tako da smo na nagovor nekih ljudi iz same uprave FK.Boraca pokrenuli inicijativu za osnivanje kluba navijaca FK Borac.Osnivacaka skupstina odrazna je u prostorijama MZ Mejdan 1 jer sam u to vrijeme ja obavljao i duznost predsjednika MKSSO Mejdan 1 tako da nije bilo problema za koristenje same sale za tu skupstinu.E sad u samom odabiru imena kumovali smo ja Greba i Zoran Pejic,na osnivackoj skupstini, sad se tacno ne sjecam klinaca sa Starcevice i Hiseta koji su izrazili zelju nama starijima da bi najvise voljeli da se nasa druzina zove Vulturesi-Lesinari. Bilo je prijedloga da se zovemo " Red Blue Army" ili  skraceno RBA.Odluku smo ipak donjeli nas trojica, Ja Greba i Zoka jer smo morali uvaziti  zelju naseg mladeg narastaja, da smo kojim slucajem drugacije odlucili ko zna kako bi se klub na kraju zvao.
Pored velikog broja omladinaca i tadasnjih predstvnika same uprave FK:Boraca, na konstituirajucoj sjednici vecinom galsova izabrali su mene za prvog predsjednika kluba navijaca FK Borca iz Banjaluke, Zorana Pejica za sekretara, Mladena Grebenara za blagajnika, a zapisnicar je bila Sanja tadasnja Zokina djevojka za koju ce mi sam Zoka poslje dosta godina reci da nije vise medu zivima.Nek joj je laka zemlja fina cura je bila i prava raja.Odmah nakon sjednice poceli smo da mastamo, krojimo planove i akcije nasih djelovanja, kako da sto bolje pripremimo nasu raju za navijanje na stadionu.

Title: Circular Energy Technique in Boxing Fighting
Description:
https://www.expertboxing.com - FREE BOXING TIPS!
https://www.fightingfootwork.com - INTENSE FOOTWORK DRILLS!
https://www.howtoboxin10days.com - learn HOW TO BOX in 10 Days
https://www.secretstopunchingpower.com - SECRET punching techniques!
https://www.30dayfightersdiet.com - get strong and LOSE WEIGHT
https://www.advancedboxingworkshop.com - ADVANCED punching power techniques and footwork

Learn how to add circular energy to all your boxing and fighting movements to improve your fighting speed, flow, rhythm, and endurance. 

Circular energy technique allow your movements to be faster and easier because you are using the same energy to cycle into other moves (allowing you to flow smooth from one move to another, whether it's an offensive fighting move or a defensive fighting move). Circular energy allows you to throw combination punches (faster, more flow, less effort) and make defensive maneuvers more slick, and also to transition between the two seamlessly (with no interruptions in your flow or rhythm).

Without circular energy technique, you would have to keep regenerating new energy with every new movement.

Title: Making a DEER FEEDER at the Crooked Post Lodge with PEANUT BARK DEER LURE and corn
Description: Steve Phillips of Phillips Outdoors is putting up a simple easy to make gravity deer feeder with Crooked Post Lodge's Alan "Crazy Al" Webb. The two hunters carry a piece of drain pipe and bungee straps deep into a remote swampy area of the property and put in a corn feeder where two game trails meet. The corn and area are sprayed with a Peanut based mineral spray, Peanut Bark Deer Attractant made by Phillips Outdoors (www.phillipsoutdoors.com) to add protein, vitamins and essential minerals that the deer will need to grow racks and remain healthy throughout the season. Title: Navigator 600 light sport aircraft from 3 Xtrim.
Description:
http://www.sportaviationmagazine.com - Navigator 600 light sport aircraft from 3 Xtrim. Dan Johnson gives us a quick look at the Navigator 600 light sport aircraft from 3 Xtrim during the E.A.A. Sport Aviation Convention at Lakeland Florida. http://www.sportaviationexpos.com

The NAVIGATOR 600 has been designed and manufactured in "3Xtrim" Aircraft Factory in Bielsko-Biala (southern Poland). It continues the 55-year tradition and experience of the world class SZD-PZL-Bielsko Glider Factory.

Adam Kurbiel, a designer of modern gliders at the SZDPZL, established the 3Xtrim Airplane Factory.

NAVIGATOR 600 is built to meet the requirements of LSA (Light Sport Airplane). On the Canadian market, NAVIGATOR 600 is known as 3X55 (since 2006) and it meets the requirements of AULA (Advance Ultra-Light Airplane).

Exceptional flying characteristics, low maintenance and operational cost, make this aircraft a perfect choice for training and pleasure fl ying. The very quiet cockpit can be equipped with latest, state of the art "Glass" instruments, radio, transponder and GPS. The 3X55 is also available with glider tow hook, amphibious fl oats, skis and dedicated trailer. Important also is the fact that the wings are removable for easy storage and transport. A large-capacity fuel tank can be installed for long cross-country flights.

NAVIGATOR 600 has succeeded in navigation sport events such as 16th World Precision Flying Championships in Herning, Denmark, August 2004. The pilot was unbeaten Christopher Wieczorek, who won the Championships and claimed the title of World Champion.

About West Bromwich Albion:

West Bromwich Albion Football Club, also known as West Brom, the Baggies, the Throstles, or simply Albion, currently play in the English Barclays Premier League. 
Established in 1878, Albion has a proud heritage and rich tradition as one of the 12 founder members of England's Football League. 

The club won the Football League Championship in 1920 and are five-time FA Cup winners (1888, 1892, 1931, 1954 & 1968).
 
Strong footballing principles remain at the core of the club and its progressive thinking has seen it thrive on and off the pitch on a global stage, while not forgetting its roots. 
 
The home of the 'Baggies' -The Hawthorns -- has a 26,586 capacity and sits in a central location in the Midlands. 
 
Like the club's state-of-the-art training facilities, the stadium offers the ideal backdrop for Barclays Premier League football.

Title: (Bowfishing) [Australia] CHEAP CHINESE 48# lb BOW MODIFY MUDCAT MOUNT
Description:
http://www.learn-archery.com/proper-draw-length.html

[view in full screen in 720p HD if able or 480p resolution] 
Mudcat bowfishing reel mounting by modification. Canoe and paddle board bow fishing practicality. This is not a long-bow and not a re-curve bow, its a "bow" (definitely not a compound bow).
Stuffed the first test shot, but that happens if there is any problem with the winds in the Dyneema fishing line, it can get caught on things easily!!! The bow i bought on "aliexpress" with a prepaid visa. I now have some soft fish arrows because the carp point arrow type(as seen here) "pulled back through(the barbs are simply thin wire)" a big Bonito when i went fishing at Coal Cliff NSW on the south coast below Sydney.
Filmed 350Km inland at Eon Dry Gulch, Australia.

A quick reminder, Australian bow-fishing is only legal in Ocean waters (is also classified as Spear-fishing and only geographical location is required to be adhered for purpose of bow-fishing) and not inland or freshwater except in South Australia but only for a pest species called Carp and only in the Murray river and tributaries for Carp. There has been talk of introducing bow fishing for Carp in other states and territories of Australia but is only in suggestion stages.

Title: Ross Levine vs. Jason Bourelly - Men's Fighting Championship - Amerikick Internationals 2011
Description: We were hoping that Levine might try a few judo throws on Bourelly as the final competitors came to the stage for the men's sparring grand championship fight.  We weren't so lucky but the fight was quite entertaining.  Levine and Bourelly spent time measuring each other as they tried to figure out the best strategy for attack.  Bourelly scored first and quickly followed his scoring hand technique with a 2-point kick.  Levine started his comeback, scoring two points.  After that, it was a point exchange with Levine tying the score at 4 after which, Bourelly landed a beautiful head kick to score two points just before the buzzer.  Wearing his SportMartialArts.com sticker, Bourelly was crowned the winner with a 6-4 score

Title: CytoSport Muscle Milk Review | Anything Special?
Description:
Visit http://rawmusclegain.com

CytoSport Muscle Milk Review.
There is a crazy amount of competition when it comes to whey protein supplements. One of bodybuilding.com's top seller is CytoSport Muscle Milk. Let's see what makes this supplement special and take a look at the label.
Looking at the label CytoSport promises 32 grams of protein, 0 lactose, and 20 different vitamins and minerals per serving. It also states that is free of any banned substances and is athlete friendly. Finally they hint that this is good to take pre workout and/ or post workout. Let's see what real consumers have been saying about muscle milk, time for some social proof.
Reported pros
1) Decent for bulking or replacing meals with
2) Helps to build muscle
3) Taste is pretty good
4) It's a solid beginner protein

Reported cons
1) A bit pricey
2) Some say there's not enough protein
3) High amount of carbs and fats
4) High in calories

So far it looks like a decent bulking supplement, let's look at the ratings. Bodybuidling.com provides a respectable 957 reviews scoring a solid 8.7. Supplementreviews.com isn't as friendly towards muscle milk, they show 107 ratings scoring a less inspiring 7.6. This gives us a total of 1064 rounding off at 8.59. Overall a pretty good score, let's look at the active ingredients.
Whey protein 
- Whey protein helps maintain a healthy body composition, fight off chronic diseases and can help you improve your emotional health.
- It is known to be the most bioavailable form of protein around
- On average this protein takes roughly 2 hours to fully digest
Whey Protein Isolate
- Highly filtered form of whey protein
- 90% of this whey protein is pure protein by weight
- This form is also lactose free and other minerals are also filtered out
Whey Peptides
- Mix of powerful isolates of amino acids derived from much longer whole whey protein molecules. It was discovered that these isolated Whey Peptides exerted the following benefits:
- More insulin-like growth factor (IGF-1) was released
- Improved overall endocrine hormone response
- A highly increased state of nitrogen utilization and retention
- More intracellular, anti-aging antioxidants
- An increased state of immune function
- Improved gastrointestinal health
- Increased muscle growth rates
Glutamine
- Amino acid that is responsible for fueling the immune system
- This amino is very helpful in avoiding the body entering a catabolic state where muscle tissue is eaten for energy.
- Also helps with the nitrogen levels in the body
- Has been tied to an increase in HGH (human growth hormone) production.
Final Verdict
It seems that this is a decent protein supplement that is mostly beneficial for those looking to bulk up. More experienced whey protein users label this protein supplement as good for beginners. The user can expect:
- Increased muscle mass
- Decreased recovery time
- Good taste
However, the draw backs to consider are:
- It's a bit pricey
- Too many carbs and fat for some
- Calorie count is rather high at 310
If you'd like to know when muscle milk goes on special, visit rawmusclegain.com and sign up using our form. We will then email you when muscle milk or any of your favorite supplements go on a substantial promotion. Thanks for watching!

Title: Time for Action - Danny Fairbrass
Description:
"I have tried to acquire lakes in England for some time, narrowly missing some great opportunities. At the same time, I am constantly saddened by the impact otters are having on big carp stocks around the country. Many people either refuse to acknowledge that there is a problem on their waters, or simply cannot justify fencing because they have no money or don't know where to start. 

It's not all doom and gloom; many people are doing great work for their own syndicates and some clubs are proactive, but I felt I could do far more to help develop new, affordable waters with quality fish that are protected from otters from day one, and also help those who cannot help themselves to protect their fish. 

I am therefore setting up a totally not-for-profit organisation initially solely funded by me personally with three main aims: 

1. To acquire leases on new waters or existing fisheries, fence them properly, stock them with quality fish and start new, low-cost syndicates populated by anglers who wish to contribute to their fishery with time and effort, as well as the cost of a ticket. As soon as these syndicates create excess money this will be used for more fish, new leases and fencing. No profit will be enjoyed by any individual. 

2. To otter fence waters run by other non-profit organisations like fishing clubs. The funding for this will initially come from my own pocket but in future I will be hosting large events up and down the country to raise money for this sole purpose. Slideshows in large venues seating more than 500 people each paying 20 pounds will easily generate enough money to fence two 10-acre waters, especially if manpower is provided by the club to work alongside ground workers employed by me to do the job right. 

In addition waters that have lost fish will receive new stock of high quality fish and those running them will be shown how to rear their own fish from spawn to create a conveyor belt of carp for the future of their club or fishery.

3. To give anglers a voice at government level working alongside groups like the Predation Action Group (PAG) and the Angling Trust. This is low priority at this time as I wish to concentrate the organisation's efforts on creating and protecting as many fisheries as possible to secure the future of our sport. The political argument will be fought over many years and in that time many fish will be lost if we just talk and don't act! 

I am looking for an, honest, passionate, and committed person to head up this organisation. No experience is required in running a fishery, although it can only help your application. 

This is a lifetime's work so only those interested in dedicating every waking moment of their working life should apply.

Salary will be totally dependant upon experience and the skills you bring to the job, but you must be a natural leader with outstanding organisational and negotiating skills as much of the role will be securing and managing new waters. 

In addition, I need groundworkers prepared to work hard for a honest day's money to develop new and protect existing fisheries, please send your CV with relevant areas of expertise. 

Finally, I ask anyone prepared to donate either time, expertise or money to get in touch and tell us what you can offer. 

I am totally committed to helping the sport I love not only survive, but thrive and expand beyond even my high expectations. 

Thank you for your attention, I look forward to your response."

If you want to apply to head up Dan's organisation then please send your CV and covering letter to elaine@korda.co.uk. Make sure you include "CV for otter group" in the subject field.

If you are a groundworker and would like to work with the organisation, then please send your CV to the above email address. 

Finally, if you can help in any way, then please send details to the same address.

Title: Afghan Cricket Team
Description:
Afghanistan's rise through the cricket world continued as they secured the Intercontinental Cup in their first year of participation with a commanding seven-wicket victory against Scotland in Dubai. Mohammad Shahzad guided the pursuit of 124 with an unbeaten 56 after Scotland had been skittled for 82.

Scotland were facing an uphill battle at the start of the third day when they resumed on 64 for 6 and the lower order couldn't turn around their fortunes. The innings lasted just a further eight overs with Mirwais Ashraf claiming three quick wickets and Hamid Hassan completing a match-haul of eight when he removed Richie Berrington.

Karim Sadiq fell early in the chase, but Scotland needed more than one breakthrough to give Afghanistan a scare. Shahzad and Shabir Noori (35) added a brisk 55 to ease any tension in the dressing room. When Noori was caught behind, Narwoz Mangal hit four boundaries to take Afghanistan to the brink of victory.

Hassan was named Man of the Match and his coach, Rashid Latif, offered him high praise with comparisons to Wasim Akram and Waqar Younis. "I kept wicket a lot with Wasim and Waqar who are both mentally and physically very strong and they used to bowl spells of 18 and 20 overs on the trot and to see Hamid come in and bowl 22 odd overs on the trot I think is amazing," he said. "I didn't think anybody could bowl 22 overs in a row, but Hamid did and it was simply great stuff."

Hassan, though, was more modest. " I don't know where I get the stamina to bowl 22 overs, I think I was just so desperate to make sure we won the final that I lost count of how many overs I had bowled," he said.

"It wasn't easy bowling as I've got a bit of a heel injury but all that mattered was that we won the final today. Credit should go to Scotland, they played well and particularly [Neil] McCallum who scored the century for Scotland on the first day."

Title: Stein Arbor Trolley : TreeStuff.com Product Detail
Description:
TreeStuff.com Review of the Stein Arbor Trolley by Reg Coates.

The Arbor Trolley is available @ https://www.treestuff.com/store/catalog.asp?item=2293

The STEIN Arbor-Trolley designed by Reg Coates is a multi-functional handling system. Designed to take the hard work out of transporting brush and logs. The Arbor-Trolley is capable of carrying up to 1000 lbs in weight and can transport the equivalent of five plus man-loads of loose brush in one. This version has been beefed up with solid tires and is now made in the USA.

At only 30" wide it is perfect for transporting material from back gardens with narrow access with ease. Not only will it speed up the transportation of brush and logs it will help reduce the debris left by dragging brash along paths. This multi-function handling system has many applications and uses to help reduce transport time and ultimately speed up the job safely.

Title: Zinedine Zidane interview on France's 2010 World Cup campaign
Description:
France legend Zinedine Zidane criticizes France's World Cup campaign. 

Zidane saying: "The problem is when things come out -- it complicates everything and the problem becomes bigger. What has happened happened, he was excluded because it is a decision from the Federation. And I do not agree with the players refusal to training. But at the same I am not there to know what's happening inside their minds. I do not agree at all because as a journalist said, the World Cup will be remembered by two things; the team that wins it and France for not training or rather refusing to train."

"If we get through, this team has the possibility, if we win this match (against South Africa) because there is the possibility that we get through and then everything can change -- everything can change for them. So, everything it has been said until now maybe they deserve it but now we are about to spit on them like never before. So maybe they deserve it a little bit. This match now for them is the most important thing. And that's why I say to myselF they know exactly where they stand. They know if they get through, things will be again like they used to be because winning helps things to be good again. If not, they will lose and come back home."

Title: Belgium vs Germany - Men's Rabobank Hockey World Cup 2014 Hague 5th/6th Place [15/6/2014]
Description:
"Belgium and Germany battled it out for 5th place at the 2014 Rabobank Men's Hockey World Cup.

Germany made good use of their first penalty corner of the game and scored through Christopher Zeller to go 1-0 up. Tom Boon scored his fifth goal of the tournament to draw Belgium level in the 25th minute from a penalty corner. The half time break arrived with the teams tied at 1-1.

Four minutes into the second half, Belgium went 2-1 up from another penalty corner this time scored by Tanguy Cosyns. Germany fought back and equalised in the 56th minute through a great solo goal from Florian Fuchs. However, three minutes later Belgium led 3-2 with Florent van Aubel scoring a field goal. Belgium's Sebastian Dockier then scored potentially the goal of the tournament with a shot from a tight angle that zoomed over the keeper's shoulder and high into the net. The 4-2 score line was enough for Belgium to secure 5th place.

Title: Michael Whitaker & GIG Amai - 2010 Olympia W.C.Q. - R.1 & Jump-off
Description:
CSI5*-W Olympia, London
World Cup Qualifier
presented by H&M
International Jumping Competition
First round with a jump-off 
Fence height: 1.60m (5 ft 3 in)

Sunday 19 December, 2010 

1) GIG Amai & Michael Whitaker (GBR) 0/0 Time 35.72
2) Tinka's Serenade & Billy Twomey (IRL) 0/0 Time 35.74
3) Le Prestige St Lois*de Hus & Kevin Staut (FRA) 0/0 Time 36.26

37 starters

The 50 year old Yorkshire-born Michael Whitaker was delighted with his horse today.  "Amai is definitely as good a horse as I've ever had, if not better.  He didn't do anything when he was nine and not a lot when he was an eight-year-old so he had a lot of catching up to do.  You've got to be patient when producing horses, and this week I put all my eggs in one basket and it paid off!  I planned for this one and it came off - that doesn't often happen - and this is a great place to win!" he said, quite overtaken with emotion.

Michael Whitaker last won the World Cup class at Olympia in 1993 riding Everest Two-Step.

Title: Kayak Fishing  it's ((( BAD TO THE BONE ))) in San Francisco Bay
Description:
Learn a trick or two , okay to watch this vid ??? 
Clicking ( THUMBS UP ) can help advise others too, enjoy and be safe guys. Remember if your not catching at least your learning, practice makes perfect.

Kayak Fishing in the San Francisco Bay with HALIBU77..........

FUN FISHING WITH FUN MUSIC
GREAT COMBO

Fishing in the San Francisco Bay on a kayak was so much fun. The weather was 80-90 degree in some parts of the Bay , but on the water 70 loved it!

I am fishing from a 2010 Hobie Mirage Revolution Kayak.  I attached a Hobie Sail to catch any breeze to help me for trolling Halibut or Stripe Bass .  On my Starboard side is a DIY outrigger made 1 1/4 PVC pipe and Heavy Duty Window Screen.

The Floats were made of several materials Crab Pot Floats , Spray Foam, heater tubing,and tape. 
This was a project that I was working on that got better and better with changes along the way.

Adding the sail to the kayak was exciting just to sit there and let the wind do the job.
This is an old video of mine that I wanted to share with all you new Kayak Anglers
that might want to try adding a sail to your Hobie kayaks.

Title: After Glow: Post Workout Supplement
Description:
http://www.sixpacksmackdown.com

This is a review for the post-workout supplement AfterGlow from BioRhythm.
The product contains 20 grams protein, 32 grams carbs, 7.5 grams glutamine, and 2:1:1 ratio BCAAs. Pretty solid lineup for a post workout drink. 
I had the watermelon flavor, and although I don't usually enjoy watermelon flavored things in general, this was pretty dang good. I would give it a 9/10 for taste. 
Overall, the product has great ingredients, and great taste. However, I just looked up the price for a 4.23 lb. tub on bodybuilding.com and its going for $125.95.  Yowsers!
I do believe it is a great product, but I, personally would never pay that price. If you can afford it, go for it. Otherwise, there are other products out there that compare pretty favorably to this one.

Bir - Billing is where I learned Paragliding. Bir is a small town in the state of Himachal Pradesh, India. It is considered as the best Paragliding site in India. Billing is name of the take-off which is at an altitude of 2300m(ASL). This place have hosted few Pre-Paragliding World Cups in the past and is preparing to host the Paragliding World Cup in 2015.-- Bir Billing have some Paragliding schools to learn from or one can just take a tandem flight with an experienced pilot. Disclaimer: Paragliding can be seriously addictive.. ;)

Some things to be aware of when installing in the TM-15:

You'll need to bend the Capacitor more to fit.
